#circuitbreakersg day 49

I have never been good at art. Not in school, not now. But I can cook, a little, I guess.
.
.
.
So here’s my humble attempt of creating some “art” with my focaccia. 🙂
.
.
.
The end result wasn’t quite what I had expected as the ingredients on the focaccia didn’t survive very well with the high heat needed to bake the bread. I will need to work on this in my next attempt. .
.
.
Good thing is that the bread is tasty (far better than the first time I made focaccia using a different recipe)! So I ended up only having the focaccia for dinner because who can resist freshly baked bread!? 😛
.
.
.
I’m thankful that it’s a non-working day today and I got to experiment with something fun in the kitchen. And we are down to the last week of circuit breaker! 💪🏻 #gratitudediary
.
.
.
Btw, let me know if you could tell what the picture is! 😃
.
.
.

I'm grateful to know grateful peeps like you esp during trying times like CB 🙆‍♀️
@ainz_gourmet haha it’s actually a landmark in Singapore.. no one has guessed it some your guess of a water mill is the closest! And it’s actually a sunset... 🤣 🤣 🤣
@28nankinstreet Ahh... Gardens by the bay? Still don’t quite get the watermill look a like tho 😅
@ainz_gourmet yes that’s correct! 🤣 the ‘watermill’ is the Singapore flyer... 😂 😂

I reckon that cooking is a piece of art too. I might not be good with drawing / colouring, but that’s what I like to think 😁

Sorry to hear the topping didn’t survive the heat. Luckily you took a picture before baking. I’ll be crying if I didn’t 😅 Looks to me like a water mill to water the plants and true in a beautiful sunny day ☺️ The texture of the focaccia looks really good. That must hav been a yummy dinner you had 😋😋 What did you hav the foc with btw?
Creative way to spice up your focaccia! 😁👍👍
